main event: A long tail, brush shaped object was observed in the sky in Duluth, Minnesota in February 1963.
interesting points: The object appeared to move slowly and was heading northward., The sighting lasted for approximately 3 seconds., The observer believed the object was not a meteor., There were multiple reports of unidentified flying objects on February 14, 1963., The object was described as larger than a jet aircraft and illuminated the area with a bright light.
sighted object: a long tail, brush shaped object
